            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "There‚Äôs no such thing as: exclusive `end_row` and exclusive `end_col`.\n\nWhen considering both `row` and `col`, an end position can only be either inclusive or exclusive, corresponding to two cases:\n\n1. (inclusive `end_row`, inclusive `end_col`)\n2. (inclusive `end_row`, exclusive `end_col`)\n\nIf the case I mentioned is not allowed, how can one use `vim.api.nvim_buf_get_text` to retrieve all the text from a buffer?\n\nNote that the buffer content is `{ \"line 1\", \"line 2\", \"\" }`, not `{ \"line 1\", \"line 2\" }`.\n\nPlease consider the logic behind this.\n",
